  <main>
    <div class="shell">
      <article class="card">
        <div class="eyebrow">Privacy</div>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
          This Privacy Policy explains how FlowClips uses information when connecting to TikTok for Developers 
          and processing creator video uploads.
        </p>

        <div class="badge-row">
          <span class="pill">Applies to: FlowClips web app</span>
          <span class="pill">Last updated: <span id="updated"></span></span>
        </div>

        <div class="sections">
          <section class="section">
            <h2>1. Information We Access</h2>
            <p>
              FlowClips connects to TikTok using OAuth. When you authorize the app, TikTok provides:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Basic account information permitted by the <strong>user.info.basic</strong> scope (such as open_id and display name).</li>
              <li>Access tokens that allow the Service to upload or publish videos on your behalf using the TikTok Content Posting API.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              FlowClips does not request or store your TikTok password.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="section">
            <h2>2. How We Use This Information</h2>
            <p>
              Information obtained via TikTok is used only to:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Confirm which TikTok account is connected.</li>
              <li>Upload creator videos to TikTok using the <strong>video.upload</strong> scope.</li>
              <li>Publish uploaded videos when you choose to do so, using the <strong>video.publish</strong> scope.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              We do not use your data for advertising, profiling, or resale.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="section">
            <h2>3. Data Sharing & Third Parties</h2>
            <p>
              FlowClips does not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. Video uploads and account 
              information are transmitted only to TikTok as required to perform the actions you trigger.
            </p>
            <p>
              TikTok may independently collect and process data under its own Terms of Service and Privacy Policy. 
              We recommend reviewing TikTok’s policies to understand how they handle your information.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="section">
            <h2>4. Data Storage & Security</h2>
            <p>
              Access tokens and minimal account identifiers may be stored by the Service to maintain your session 
              and to run your publishing workflow. Reasonable technical measures are used to protect this information 
              from unauthorized access.
            </p>
            <p>
              Because the Service depends on your TikTok authorization, revoking the app’s access in your TikTok 
              account settings will prevent further use of the tokens.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="section">
            <h2>5. Cookies & Analytics</h2>
            <p>
              FlowClips does not use third-party analytics, advertising cookies, or tracking pixels. The Service is 
              focused solely on enabling your connection to TikTok and handling video uploads and publishing.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="section">
            <h2>6. Your Choices</h2>
            <p>You can:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Disconnect FlowClips from TikTok by revoking access in your TikTok account settings.</li>
              <li>Stop using the Service at any time.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              If you disconnect the app, FlowClips will no longer be able to upload or publish videos to your TikTok account.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="section">
            <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
            <p>
              This Privacy Policy may be updated to reflect changes to the Service or TikTok’s platform requirements. 
              Updates will be posted on this page with an updated “Last updated” date.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="section">
            <h2>8. Contact</h2>
            <p>
              If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or how FlowClips uses data from TikTok for Developers, 
              please contact the app owner using the contact information provided in the TikTok Developer portal.
            </p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </article>

